title: -Fast Neutron Scattering Cross Sections of Sn-118 At 14.9 and 18.0 Mev.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Jour. of Nuclear Science and Technology, Vol.25, Issue.6, p.511 (1988)

x4freetext: -FAST NEUTRON SCATTERING CROSS SECTIONS OF SN-118
WERE ACCELERATED TO 12.2 AND 15.5 MEV, RESPECTIVELY,
WITH AN AVERAGE BEAM CURRENT OF 2 MICROAMPS. THE BEAM
WAS PULSED AT A REPETITION RATE OF 2 MHZ.
A DEUTERIUM GAS TARGET, FILLED TO A PRESSURE OF
2 ATM, WAS USED TO PRODUCE NEUTRONS OF ENERGIES 14.9
TIME-OF-FLIGHT WITH A FLIGHT PATH OF 8 M. OVER-
THE SCATTERED NEUTRONS WERE DETECTED BY AN ARRAY
OF FOUR NE 213 LIQUID SCINTILLATORS, 20 CM DIAMETER BY
35 CM THICK, VIEWED BY PM-TUBES AT BOTH ENDS. TIME
COMPENSATION TECHNIQUES WERE USED. THE COVERED ANGULAR
TWO NE 213 SCINTILLATORS, 5 CM DIAMETER BY 1.26
CM THICK, WERE USED AS MONITOR DETECTORS.
.THE SAMPLE WAS OF CYLINDRICAL SHAPE, 1.6 CM IN
DIAMETER AND 3.0 CM IN HEIGHT. THE ISOTOPIC PURITY OF
THE SAMPLE WAS 97.15 PERCENT. THE CHEMICAL PURITY WAS
.THE DATA WERE CORRECTED FOR DEAD TIME, SOURCE NEUTRON
ANISOTROPY, FLUX ATTENUATION, MULTIPLE SCATTERING AND
